<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9856410981547></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9856410981547><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9856410981547>RE: Equiping my mage</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9856410981547#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 26th 4:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fighting willowisps is a good moneymaker for level 8-12, but frankly, you can do better after level 12. Frankly, the wisps do not drop greater lightstones all that frequently. You'll be lucky to get one greater lightstone per 7-10 kills, and the experience slows to a crawl after level 12 or so.<br><br>Lavastorm is a great mage-friendly money zone. Keep a dimensional pocket for dervish rocks, and sell those off to the gypsies for 4gp apiece. The other loot is lightweight, stackable, and (except for fire drake scales) sells for anywhere from 3gp to 1pp apiece. Gems, eggs, sacs of bile, more gems (lots of gems in this zone). Drakes and rock dervishes will also drop coin, averaging about 2gp apiece. It doesn't sound like just a whole lot, but the mobs drop lots of loot, so it all really adds up. You don't kill a green mob only to find out it has a "burned out lightstone" on it.<br><br>Higher level elementals and lava crawlers will also drop research words, pages, and runes, so it's a good way to start up a collection. I found a nice collection of level 16-20 words.<br><br>A big, big advantage of this zone is that most of the loot stacks, so you can just pile it in the bank and sell it to your guild merchants when you go back to buy your next round of spells.<br><br>If you have no love for dark elves, there is a dark elven guard outside the entrance to Lavastorm who spawns in the level 14-17 range. You and your level 16 pet will take him down with ease, and he'll respawn right about the time you get up to full mana. He also *always* drops a bronze longsword, so you get a little experience and a guaranteed 2pp5gp per kill. <br><br>By the time you've finished getting experience from this zone, you're ready to carefully start picking off gargoyles in the Ocean of Tears. They seem to drop an average of one gargoyle eye per two kills, so that's a 4pp kill with good experience. If you've been soloing up to this point, you'll know how to keep from getting frenzied by the other gargoyles.<br><br>Then, of course, you hit your high 20s/early 30s and start buying gems for focus items, and it's back to practicing your begging skill on the merchants, but that's another story =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
